  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Familial hypercholesterolemia (FH), an inherited disorder of lipoprotein metabolism, is a
      risk for early cardiovascular disease (CVD). This autosomal dominant disease is characterized
      by markedly elevated plasma concentrations of low density lipoprotein (LDL) and total
      cholesterol (TC). The purpose of this study is to compare the effect of a diet low in
      saturated fats but enriched either with rapeseed oil (RO) or sunflower oil (SO) in children
      and adolescents with FH on serum lipoproteins.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
